                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4720.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-26T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A suspension of constitutional guaranties equivalent to martial law took effect
                    to-day over about one-third of the Republic. Press censorship exists at all
                    interior points. Between Torreon and Chihuahua all communication has again been
                    cut, communication with the city alone remaining undisturbed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
